# Summon + skhd example
# Add these lines to your ~/.skhdrc
#
# The Hyper key (cmd + alt + ctrl + shift) is a popular choice for app-switching
# bindings because almost no application uses it for its own shortcuts.
#
# Requires: https://github.com/koekeishiya/skhd

# --- App switching (Hyper key) ---

hyper - return : summon terminal
hyper - b      : summon browser
hyper - z      : summon editor
hyper - f      : summon finder
hyper - n      : summon notes

# --- Expanded form (if your skhd version doesn't support "hyper") ---

cmd + alt + ctrl + shift - return : summon terminal
cmd + alt + ctrl + shift - b      : summon browser
cmd + alt + ctrl + shift - z      : summon editor
cmd + alt + ctrl + shift - f      : summon finder
